author: makortel
body:
#### PR description:

I was looking a failed header consistency check report elsewhere, and noticed complaints
```
src/DataFormats/Candidate/interface/iterator.h:55:24: warning: inline function 'reco::Candidate& reco::candidate::iterator::operator*() const' used but never defined
   55 |       inline reference operator*() const;
      |                        ^~~~~~~~
>> Compiling src/DataFormats/EcalDigi/interface/EBSrFlag.h 
In file included from src/DataFormats/Candidate/interface/const_iterator.h:10:
/data/cmsbld/jenkins/workspace/ib-run-pr-tests/CMSSW_13_1_X_2023-04-05-1100/src/DataFormats/Candidate/interface/iterator.h:55:24: warning: inline function 'reco::Candidate& reco::candidate::iterator::operator*() const' used but never defined
   55 |       inline reference operator*() const;
      |                        ^~~~~~~~
src/DataFormats/Candidate/interface/const_iterator.h:60:24: warning: inline function 'const reco::Candidate& reco::candidate::const_iterator::operator*() const' used but never defined
   60 |       inline reference operator*() const;
      |                        ^~~~~~~~
```

According to `git grep` the `DataFormats/Candidate/interface/iterator.h` and `DataFormats/Candidate/interface/const_iterator.h` are not used anywhere, so simplest fix seems to be removing them.

#### PR validation:

None
title: Remove DataFormats/Candidate/interface/iterator.h as unused
